The Sultan of Sokoto, Muhammad  Sa’ad Abubakar,  has stressed the need to strengthen  enforcement of road safety rules and  enhance protection of   lives and properties. He also urged government officials to enlighten  their convoy drivers on obedience to traffic rules and  regulations. He was speaking in Sokoto yesterday when he received  the Federal Road Safety Corps’ Zonal Commander for Sokoto, Kebbi and Zamfara Dr Kayode Olagunju at his palace. Sultan calls for improved road safety VIP convoys careless, cause road crashes  – Sultan FRSC, others flag off ‘Operation Eagle Eye’ in Sokoto